were especially helpful in meeting the challenges. </div><div class="t m19e x18 h1e y1c4 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What can you do now to prepare for present or future challenges to your </div><div class="t m19f x63 h1e y1c5 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">faith? List two approaches on the lines below. </div><div class="t m1a0 x68 h1f y1c6 ff1 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">In</div><div class="t m1a1 x63 h13 y1c7 ff1 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">FURTHER STUDY AND MEDITATION: </div><div class="t m1a2 x55 h1e y1c8 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Review how Jesus acted </div><div class="t m1a3 x63 h1e y1c9 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">when under attack. See 1 Peter 2:20-25; John 19:1-11. Read &quot;Persecution </div><div class="t m1a4 x13 h1e y1ca ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the First Centuries,&quot; in </div><div class="t m1a5 x1c h1e y1cb ff7 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Great Controversy, </div><div class="t m1a6 x2d h1e y1cc ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">chapter 2, pp. 39-48. </div><div class="t m1a7 x63 h13 y1cd ff1 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUMMARY: </div><div class="t m122 x69 h1e y1ce ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The devil has continually attacked Christ and His church. </div><div class="t m1a8 x63 h1e y1cf ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As Christ has triumphed in the past, so He will triumph in the future. There </div><div class="t m18a x13 h1e y1d0 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">will be an army of the faithful ones whom He will take to His heavenly </div><div class="t m1a9 x63 h1e y1d1 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">home. </div><div class="t m1aa x13 h13 y132 ff1 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
